I love this place. It's gonna run you about $20 a person, but that's life in the 2020s... good, fresh food is worth it. The turkey melt and the breakfast chimi... delicious.
I'm in Denver for 6 months and while I'm here, Caitlin's is my joint.

detailedReviews.author: Royal
detailedReviews.text: This place is absolutely amazing with the best food and service in Denver! Ricky is always there to greet you with a smile and make you feel like family! It is a must stop for anyone who is visiting the area, and our favorite local restaurant!

detailedReviews.author: Mark Peterson

detailedReviews.author: Steve Lavin
detailedReviews.text: Excellent breakfast. Cynthia was a great waitress, friendly and efficient.

detailedReviews.author: Tracey
detailedReviews.text: The service was not that great. I ordered the breakfast burrito with the carne adovada. The carne adovada was like a pork chop not tender as one would expect. I had red and green chile on my burrito. The burrito had no flavor at all, I kept putting salt and pepper on it. On top of all that the prices were kind of high in my opinion.

detailedReviews.author: Laila Alizadeh
detailedReviews.text: My wife ordered us breakfast from here this morning...over $40 for two people. They forgot to bring a drink and then put 200 pieces of tomatoes in my omelet that was to have NO TOMATO. The hashbrown was burnt to hell and hard and has no seasoning. It also was thrown together like slop. Will never order from here again.  I could have got my order correct at IHOP and enjoyed a breakfast for way less $. Threw it in the trash.

detailedReviews.author: Corey Chandler
detailedReviews.text: Had a breakfast burrito was pretty tasteless. Ordered Togo no silverware or napkins for a 17 dollar burrito. Green chili is void of all flavor taste like thick corn starch with chicken water.  I recommend salt on everything and taking people's purchases a little more serious have some pride in your work.

detailedReviews.author: Mark Cole
detailedReviews.text: Had never heard of this place before, now I‚Äôm glad I found it. Hash browns 100 % better than Waffle House. Will definitely be back!

detailedReviews.text: This place is just ok. For the price of the food and the quality and quantity it is better to go elsewhere. I pay less to go to snooze which in my opinion blows this place out of the water. My suggestion is to lower the prices of this place to reflect the food service and location. Food lines up with IHOP but with a higher price point.

detailedReviews.author: Melinda Wolfe
detailedReviews.text: I ordered the mile high deluxe and it was 80% hash browns. 10% carne asada and a splash of terrible green chili. I don't understand how this place is packed with the food is so bad. For $18 a plate the food needs to be much better.

detailedReviews.author: Dalia Rosales
detailedReviews.text: Ordered online the carne asada.  I got two or three pieces of meat on a plate of about 2lbs of hash browns lathered up in so much butter I‚Äôm still trying to figure out a way to get rid of the taste in my mouth. We also ordered the stacked enchiladas and we were confused if the chicken was meant to be shredded or diced/cubed;  there were all sorts inside them.  Very bland taste.  Oh and almost forgot to mention the carne asada was suppose to come with a tortilla that we didn‚Äôt get.  First and last time trying this place.  Complete bummer as I live right around the corner from them.

detailedReviews.author: Rian Williams
detailedReviews.text: I loved the breakfast chimichanga. Im not normally into chimichangas but they put scrambled eggs and your choice of meat inside and it was fantastic. I loved that it came with sour cream and guac. The lady that served me was very nice. Good green chili and coffee too.

detailedReviews.author: Jim Conley
detailedReviews.text:
Colorful breakfast/lunch restaurant with a Mexican slant. Very good omelets and benedicts. The Bell omelet is full of various meats and has a wonderful taste. It comes with hash browns which are covered with cheese and toast. It's a filling breakfast. The coffee is average.

Service is fast and friendly. The space is nicely decorated and includes both tables and booths. There are a few TVs. They do have password protected Wi-Fi. There's also a patio out back.

There's plenty of parking in the lot in front of the restaurant.

detailedReviews.author: Tanya Krivtsova
detailedReviews.text: I ordered through Uber Eats and was entirely disappointed by the food. I got a breakfast burrito and the giant cinnamon roll. The breakfast burrito was tiny and next to it a ridiculous side of hashbrowns. Although they did smother everything with a good amount of green chili, NOTHING was seasoned. The chili was as bland as could be. The inside of the burrito was completely bland, the hashbrowns didn't even taste salted. As for the cinnamon roll, I don't think it actually qualifies as one. The dough looked like a box-mix bread dough, upon tasting it, I'm pretty positive it WAS a box-mix bread dough. Entirely disappointed in the food from every perspective.

detailedReviews.author: BrittanyJ216

detailedReviews.author: Anthony G.

detailedReviews.text: The chicken club quesadilla I ordered for lunch was full of wonderfully balanced flavors. Bacon is a strong taste, so I was happy to find the chicken wasn't overseasoned so they could mesh together correctly. The filling was portioned out so there weren't any empty bites. It wasn't too heavy or too light. Overall it was a very satifsying lunch meal.

detailedReviews.author: Anthony Nolletti

detailedReviews.author: Holly N

detailedReviews.author: A Google User
detailedReviews.text: This place is ok for what it is.. food is decent.. but my only complaint is that the server was insanely awful. It took the server forever to acknowledge that I was here,  didn't check on me and didn't even bring me my check.. I had to go to the front for it etc. It wasn't even that busy..son there was no reason for any of the to happen.

detailedReviews.author: D
detailedReviews.text: Doing pretty good!

detailedReviews.author: Kat Kat
detailedReviews.text: I was looking for something that would be priced fairly to the quality and quantity of food.    I thought at 11am on a Sunday, most places would be packed. Caitlins had room for us, no wait, and we were immediately greeted, seated and waited on.  The food was so good.   I'll definitely be back.  I ordered the 2 eggs plate and shared with my 4yo son. It was plenty for us.  My husband ordered steak and eggs and was happy with his.  The only negative I'd give, and maybe it was just a mishap on this day, it was so hot inside I didn't want to drink my coffee.  I was slightly sweating the entire time I ate.  But regardless, I'll definitely be back.

detailedReviews.author: Crypto Moves
detailedReviews.text:
Ordered the steak and eggs with hashbrowns and sourdough toast. Good quality food, decent portions and super fast service.

I did order the steak medium rare and it came out medium well. I didn't mind but maybe they shouldn't ask what temp when ordering.

Hash browns were perfectly crispy and sunny side up eggs were perfectly cooked.

detailedReviews.author: Cain Casarez

Once we finally got the food. My omelet had raw egg spots everywhere.

detailedReviews.author: Connor McNulty

detailedReviews.author: Kelsey Weaver
detailedReviews.text:
Visiting Denver with my husband. Came to Caitlin‚Äôs for breakfast. Husband got the chicken and waffles. Although delightful, his waffle had a slightly burnt corner. I had the Eggs Benedict; also quite delicious. We very much enjoyed our experience here.

The coffee is SO GOOD. I cannot express enough how AWESOME the coffee is.

detailedReviews.author: Arica Evans
detailedReviews.text: Stacked chicken enchiladas were absolutely delicious! Service was so awesome and helpful. Best breakfast I could've imagined. Beans were so good. Definitely a worthwhile stop, would for sure visit again!

detailedReviews.author: Austin Burwick

detailedReviews.author: John Wodetzki
detailedReviews.text:
The server was amazing, and the food was microwaveable. I know this is a local spot but the ambience is a kids room at a church, the dish wear is mismatched, and even though the server was nice it still took way too long to be seen by my server as they stood and talked to the owner or manager of the restaurant. Just skip this place and make biscuits and gravy at home. You‚Äôll have a better experience and not have to deal with the worst decor in denver

Side note, do not order ‚ÄúMexican food‚Äù from here under ANY circumstances. Don‚Äôt let Denver do you like that

detailedReviews.author: Katy M
detailedReviews.text: Every time I go home to visit my family in Denver. I make sure to stop here for breakfast! The food is always good and the service too. I usually get a traditional breakfast which consists of pancakes, eggs, and bacon. My friend, who came with me last time had the huevos rancheros, and had nothing but great things to say!

detailedReviews.author: Na Green
detailedReviews.text: I ordered biscuits and gravy, eggs, and hash browns. There were no veggie options as I don‚Äôt eat pork. The biscuits and gravy had zero flavor. Tasted like something you‚Äôd feed a cat. Luckily I was able to use my discount so I didn‚Äôt feel like I completely wasted my money. Hash browns were crispy at my request but also a tad flavorless.

detailedReviews.author: Kipp Castaing

detailedReviews.author: David Littlejohn
detailedReviews.text: Great food and staff

detailedReviews.author: Ryan Weber
detailedReviews.text: Amazing breakfast burritos ü§§

detailedReviews.author: Herman Rooth

detailedReviews.author: Roger Brockevelt
detailedReviews.text: Great food and good service. Love the green chili.

detailedReviews.author: Amber Dover
detailedReviews.text: Best burritos I‚Äôve ever had!

detailedReviews.author: Joellen Lucchese
detailedReviews.text: A hidden gem!  If you are in Denver, don‚Äôt miss this place. My breakfast was absolutely delicious!!

detailedReviews.author: Tom 5280
detailedReviews.text: I don't often write reviews, but Caitlin's deserves a shout-out.  A recent brunch showed Caitlin's to be a standout with friendly service, a clean and uplifting atmosphere, and a menu that surpasses expectations of the typical diner.   I will gladly visit this neighborhood gem again and would recommend you do likewise.

detailedReviews.author: Sarah Fernandez
detailedReviews.text: I love Caitlin's. It's a family-run business and you can really feel that when you're there. The servers are unbelievably kind and warm, and the whole environment makes you feel like you're really at a neighborhood spot. I often go there to work and eat/drink coffee, and they let me sit as long as I want. They have good wifi and give free refills. The food is also very good for the most part, but sometimes is a little bit heavy, even for a diner. I love it here though, and will be coming back for a long time.

detailedReviews.author: Brian Cadieux
detailedReviews.text: Caitlin's is great.  I had the Mile High with Ham, sourdough, and 2 extra overeasy eggs with green chili.  I also had a peppermint mocha.  Everything was great!  Service was great!  Restaurant is clean.  A great place to walk to if you are waiting on your BMW maintenance.

detailedReviews.author: Chris Shelton, MSc
detailedReviews.text: Really enjoyed eating breakfast here. Just found it randomly in Google maps and went in and found it quiet, chill and the staff helpful and on top of it.
